**Image:** **CURRICULUM VITAE**

**Name:** Iranna Neerajddi
**Mobile:** +91-8668270411
**Email:** iranna.neerajddi@gmail.com
**Email:** veerumm1212@gmail.com

**Synopsis:**

*   Over 2 years of experience in Electrothermal model and Impedance matrix for 10 HD/LV Battery, Fuel cell system and Quality Assurance of Drive Train Elements.
*   Experienced in handling modeling software like Saber for DC fast charging Battery Pack Estimation and HV system simulation.
*   Hands-on with various application software’s such as ANSYS 3D, Saber and NX for design Validation and Optimization of Electro-mechanical devices used in Electric Motors.
*   Worked in High voltage Battery modeling and Impedance matrix creation of collector plates.
*   Presently working as “Assistant System Engineer” at Tata Consultancy Services (General Motors), Bangalore.

**EDUCATION**

*   September 2019 – September 2021: Master’s degree (MTech) in Electrical and Electronics Engineering, University Visvesvaraya College of Engineering (UVCE), Bangalore - 560001.
*   August 2014 – July 2018: Bachelor of Engineering (B.E) in Electrical and Electronics Engineering,  Visvesvaraya Technological University Belagavi (SKSVMA CET College of Engineering), Laxmeshwar, Karnataka.

**TECHNICAL SKILLS**

*   ANSYS 3D 2021 R1
*   Saber 20.0.1
*   ANSYS Work Bench (Structural/Modal Analysis)
*   Solid works and Siemens NX

**LANGUAGES**

*   English
*   Kannada
*   Hindi




-----

**Image:** CURRICULUM VITAE

1.  Worked as "Trainee Quality Engineer" in Divgi Torq Systems Pvt Ltd., Sirsi, Karnataka from November 2018 to September 2019. 
Key Roles:
*   Execute the Root cause & problem solving, Line Audit, Dock Audit, Setup approval, Product Audit, Final Inspection and Documentation.
*   Provide consistent solutions to the various problems of Quality Issues/ Non-conformance & follow up for the client satisfaction.
*   Execute the work on Automotive Core Tools such as FMEA, APQP, 7QC Tools, Lean Management and PPAP.
*   Etiquette in AWD Transfer cases and knowledge on Drive systems.

2.  Currently working as “Assistant Engineer” in Tata Consultancy Services (General Motors), Since February-2022. 
Role & Responsibility:
*   1-D Plant Model (Battery Thermal management) for Electric vehicle.
*   Execute the work on Low voltage Fuse analysis for the application of EV.
*   Create detailed Electrothermal model and Impedance matrix for 1-D HV Battery system and Fuel cell system.
*   Execute the DC fast charging, Range estimation and HV system simulation of Battery Pack for HEV, PHEV, BEV-Truck Modules.
*   Support for team members to prepare detailed work documentation.

DECLARATION
I hereby declare that all the relevant information mentioned here is true to my knowledge and belief.

Place: Bangalore
Date:
Iranna Neejadii


-----
